# Architecture

- Keep native shell, workspace core, plugins, terminal, LSP, and editor island as separate modules under `src/features/` and `src/core/`.
- Prefer small modules and explicit TEA (Model/Msg/update) state.
- Do not import VS Code workbench code into the native shell.
- WebView is allowed only for the editor island (and later heavy previews), never the whole shell.
- Every feature declares a manifest (`feature.json`) with mode, activation, memory, and process budgets.
